  "text": "However, nonassociativity seems not always problematic. For instance, in [CITATION_1] , in the context of reachability analysis, Yeh investigates a state space reduction technique for processes by adding distinguished actions for suspending and resuming processes; in the resulting theory, parallel composition is nonassociative. In [CITATION_2] , Kuske & Meinecke introduce a nonassociative product operator on branching automata [CITATION_3] with costs. Finally, the Orc orchestration language has three combinators to express parallel execution, two of which are nonassociative (and noncommutative) by design, because they involve a form of sequentiality [CITATION_4] .",
